net.markenwerk.commons.iterators

Interface LookAhead<Payload>

  • Type Parameters:
    Payload - The payload type.

    public interface LookAhead<Payload>
    A LookAhead is a simple container that holds the current and the next payload object of an LookAheadIterator.
    Since:
    1.1.6
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Payload get()
      Returns the current payload object of an LookAheadIterator.
      Payload getNext()
      Returns the next payload object of an LookAheadIterator.
      boolean hasNext()
      Returns whether this LookAhead has a next payload object.
      boolean isLast()
      Returns whether this LookAhead has a no next payload object.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        Payload get()
        Returns the current payload object of an LookAheadIterator.
        Returns:
        The current payload object. May be null.

      • getNext

        Payload getNext()
         throws NoSuchElementException
        Returns the next payload object of an LookAheadIterator. The returned value is not meaningful, if this LookAhead has no LookAhead#hashCode() next payload object.
        Returns:
        The next payload object. May be null.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - If this LookAhead has no next payload object.

      • hasNext

        boolean hasNext()
        Returns whether this LookAhead has a next payload object.
        Returns:
        Whether this LookAhead has a next payload object.

      • isLast

        boolean isLast()
        Returns whether this LookAhead has a no next payload object.
        Returns:
        Whether this LookAhead has a no next payload object.
